scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Which I made known to Lucius, ere the stroke
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Of this yet scarce-cold battle, at this instant
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Is full accomplish'd; for the Roman eagle,
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: From south to west on wing soaring aloft,
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Lessen'd herself, and in the beams o' the sun
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: So vanish'd: which foreshow'd our princely eagle,
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: The imperial Caesar, should again unite
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: His favour with the radiant Cymbeline,
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Which shines here in the west.
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Laud we the gods;
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: And let our crooked smokes climb to their nostrils
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: From our blest altars. Publish we this peace
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: To all our subjects. Set we forward: let
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: A Roman and a British ensign wave
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Friendly together: so through Lud's-town march:
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: And in the temple of great Jupiter
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Our peace we'll ratify; seal it with feasts.
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Set on there! Never was a war did cease,
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.

line_text: Ere bloody hands were wash'd, with such a peace.
scene_title: SCENE V.  Cymbeline's tent.
